SIMPLE: inflammatory
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inflammatory
<hw>In*flam"ma*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>inflammatoire</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Tending to inflame,
kindle, or irritate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tending to excite anger, animosity, tumult, or
sedition; seditious; <as>as, <ex>inflammatory</ex> libels, writings,
speeches, or publications</as>.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Accompanied with, or tending to
cause, preternatural heat and excitement of arterial action; <as>as, an
<ex>inflammatory</ex> disease</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Inflammatory crust</b></col>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <cd>Same
as <cref>Buffy coat</cref>, under <er>Buffy</er>.</cd> --
<col><b>Inflammatory fever</b></col>, <cd>a variety of fever due to
inflammation.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inflatable</ent>⟦br⟧
